body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Dealership Support. My name is Donald Lewis. May I ask for your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi, my name is Samantha Green.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Samantha. Could you please provide me with your phone number so we can assist you further?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five, two three four, nine six one zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for that information. Can you also share your email address with us, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is s.greene@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing your contact details, Samantha. Is there anything else we can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling nervous about the data management issue. Can you provide some guidance?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Absolutely, we're here to help you. Let's work together to resolve the data management concerns. Thank you for reaching out, Samantha. We appreciate your time and trust in us.
